body:
Certain Object Model (OM) annotations are considered "weak" and should not block removal. Others are considered "hard" and should block removal.

An example of a "weak" annotation is `OMReferenceTarget`. However, currently this will block removal. Consider the following:

```
FIRRTL version 3.2.0
circuit Foo: %[[
  {
    "class": "freechips.rocketchip.objectmodel.OMIRFileAnnotation",
    "filename": "omir.json"
  },
  {
    "class": "freechips.rocketchip.objectmodel.OMIRAnnotation",
    "nodes": [
      {
        "info": "",
        "id": "OMID:1",
        "fields": [
          {"info": "", "name": "a", "value": "OMReferenceTarget:~Foo|Foo>c"}
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
]]
  module Foo:
    input a: UInt<1>
    output b: UInt<1>

    node c = a
    connect b, c
```

Currently this will compile to:

```verilog
// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.53.0-204-g3b6f737c3-dirty
module Foo(
  input  a,
  output b
);

  wire c = a;
  assign b = c;
endmodule


// ----- 8< ----- FILE "omir.json" ----- 8< -----

[
  {
    "info": "UnlocatableSourceInfo",
    "id": "OMID:1",
    "fields": [
      {
        "info": "UnlocatableSourceInfo",
        "name": "a",
        "value": "OMReferenceTarget:~Foo|Foo>c"
      }
    ]
  }
]
```

However, it is entirely legal, and more optimal, to compile this to:

```verilog
// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.53.0-204-g3b6f737c3-dirty
module Foo(
  input  a,
  output b
);

  assign b = a;
endmodule


// ----- 8< ----- FILE "omir.json" ----- 8< -----

[
  {
    "info": "UnlocatableSourceInfo",
    "id": "OMID:1",
    "fields": [
      {
        "info": "UnlocatableSourceInfo",
        "name": "a",
        "value": "OMDeleted:"
      }
    ]
  }
]
```

This is likely the same issue as https://github.com/llvm/circt/issues/6060, just presented as an end-to-end `firtool` example.
